sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant publisher as Artifact publisher
  participant jfrog as JFrog Artifactory
  participant intake as Registry webhook or sync intake
  participant queue as PostgreSQL catalog_event_queue
  participant worker as Java indexer and reconciler
  participant journal as PostgreSQL catalog and ingestion journal
  participant sse as Authorized SSE stream
  participant ui as Registry UI

  publisher->>jfrog: Upload immutable archive, documentation, manifest, checksum, and APM properties
  publisher->>jfrog: Publish registry.catalog.ready only after all content is complete
  jfrog->>intake: Deliver signed artifact or property event
  intake->>intake: Enforce payload size, content type, HMAC, origin, subscription, repository, and safe path

  alt intake validation fails
    intake-->>jfrog: Reject without queue publication
  else event is valid
    intake->>queue: Insert normalized payload, unique transport ID, and semantic SHA-256 key
    alt exact or semantic duplicate
      queue-->>intake: Return existing publication identity
    else new event
      queue->>queue: Commit and pg_notify registry_catalog_work
      queue-->>intake: Durable publication accepted
    end
    intake-->>jfrog: HTTP 202
  end

  worker->>queue: Claim available row with FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED and a lease token
  queue-->>worker: Event payload and claim identity
  worker->>jfrog: Re-read file information, properties, manifest, documentation, and archive through JFrog Java Client
  jfrog-->>worker: Current authoritative artifact state
  worker->>worker: Validate digest, immutability, schema, UTF-8, archive safety, and APM assignments

  alt artifact is safe and complete
    worker->>journal: Transactionally upsert package, version, docs, symbols, access, statistics, lifecycle, and audit data
    worker->>journal: Mark version active and ingestion event completed
    worker->>queue: Complete matching lease and retain terminal history
    journal->>sse: PostgreSQL notification after commit
    sse-->>ui: Authorized catalog-change event
    ui->>ui: Invalidate only affected TanStack Query keys
  else terminal governance or integrity failure
    worker->>journal: Record quarantine reason and immutable evidence
    worker->>queue: Move event to dead_letter
  else transient JFrog or database failure
    worker->>queue: Release claim with bounded timestamp retry
  end

  loop incremental and nightly reconciliation
    worker->>jfrog: Compare governed Artifactory state
    worker->>journal: Compare catalog projections and repair missing hints
  end
